notesStmt.note: This is an illuminated and illustrated copy of the Collection of poems (dīvān) by Shams al-Dīn Muḥammad Ḥāfiz al-Shīrāzī (fl. eighth century AH / fourteenth CE), written in the first half of the eleventh century AH / seventeenth CE. There are five illustrations.

msContents.textLang: The primary language in this manuscript is Persian.

msItem.title: Dīvān-i Ḥāfiẓ
ديوان حافظ

title.note: Text begins on fol. 17b; inscription on fol. 6b reads: Qaṣāʾid-i Khvājah Ḥāfiẓ Shīrāzī

msItem.incipit: الا يا ايها الساقى ادر كاسا وناولها...
msItem.note: Misbound; first two folios (without text) supplied later

handDesc.handNote: Written in black nastaʿlīq script; the words ayḍan and wa-lahu in white

decoDesc.decoNote: Five illustrations; double-page illuminated incipits with headpieces; illuminated headpiece (added later); panels for chapter/section headings, cloud-bands, borders with foliate design; frame

decoNote.title: Double-page illuminated incipit with headpiece
decoNote.note: The inscription in the headpiece reads: Qaṣāʾid-i Khvājah Ḥāfiẓ Shīrāzī.

decoNote.title: Double-page illuminated incipit with headpiece
decoNote.note: The inscription in the headpiece reads: fa-Allāh khayr ḥāfiẓan.

decoNote.title: A festive party in a garden with dance, music, and wine
Majnūn seated in the wilderness with Laylá on a camel
Rustam rescuing Bīzhan from the well

binding.p: Probably twelfth century AH / eighteenth CE; dark brown leather (with flap); gold-tooled and -painted central rectangular panel and frames

origin.origDate: First half of the 11th century AH / 17th CE

history.provenance: Seal impression: ʿAbd Allāh al-Murādī, 1132 AH / 1719 CE (fol. 91b)
